Package: PlotRichness
Type: Package
Title: Species Retrieval from Open-Source Databases.
Version: 0.1.0
Author: person("Shaya", "Van Houdt", email = "shaya.v.h@gmail.com",
                  role = c("aut", "cre"), comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-4290-3593"))
Maintainer: Shaya van Houdt <shaya.v.h@gmail.com>
Description: This package uses open source databases like the Global Biodiversity 
            Information Facility (GBIF), Natura2000, and SpeciesLink to retrieve species data
            on the plot level. Using the different functions, one can find out if there is 
            information on species in a plot, and if so what their associated International 
            Union for Conservation of Nature (IUCN) status is. 
License: No license
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Imports: sp, rgbif, rgeos, rgdal, raster, wellknown, CoordinateCleaner, countrycode, dplyr, ggplot2
RoxygenNote: 7.2.3
